info.headline: Special Weather Statement issued September 17 at 3:20PM EDT by NWS Miami
info.description: ...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of east central Palm Beach County through 345 PM EDT... At 320 PM EDT, National Weather Service meteorologists were tracking a strong thunderstorm over Royal Palm Beach, or near Wellington, moving northeast at 15 mph. HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph. SOURCE...Radar indicated. IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around unsecured objects. Locations impacted include... West Palm Beach, Wellington, Palm Beach Gardens, Riviera Beach, Palm Beach, Greenacres, Royal Palm Beach, Palm Springs, Haverhill, Cloud Lake, Palm Beach International Airport, Golden Lakes, Loxahatchee Groves, Gun Club Estates, Schall Circle, Royal Palm Estates, Lake Belvedere Estates, The Acreage, Lake Clarke Shores and Glen Ridge. MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH
info.instruction: These winds can down small tree limbs and branches, and blow around unsecured small objects. Seek shelter in a safe building until the storm passes.
